Prints Model Cook's Distances Summary

# S3 method for auditor_model_cooksdistance
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

an object 'auditor_model_cooksdistance' created with model_cooksdistance function.
...

other parameters

Examples

dragons <- DALEX::dragons[1:100, ]

# fit a model
model_lm <- lm(life_length ~ ., data = dragons)

# create an explainer
exp_lm <- DALEX::explain(model_lm, data = dragons, y = dragons$life_length)
#> Preparation of a new explainer is initiated
#>   -> model label       :  lm  (default)
#>   -> data              :  100  rows  8  cols 
#>   -> target variable   :  100  values 
#>   -> predict function  :  yhat.lm  will be used (default)
#>   -> predicted values  :  numerical, min =  585.8311 , mean =  1347.787 , max =  2942.307  
#>   -> residual function :  difference between y and yhat (default)
#>   -> residuals         :  numerical, min =  -88.41755 , mean =  -1.489291e-13 , max =  77.92805  
#> A new explainer has been created!

# calculate score
model_cooksdistance(exp_lm)
#> Model label:  lm 
#> 
#> Observations with the largest Cook's distances:

#> 29      0.25442439    29
#> 7       0.25442439     7
#> 96      0.06660468    96
#>

#>          60%          70%          80%          90%         100% 
#> 7.817431e-03 1.010589e-02 1.889047e-02 3.226451e-02 2.544244e-01
